Notes on Framework update process.

Frameworks are build using libraries from libsrc subdirectory of top-level directory.
Please specify the oldest possible OSX SDK (for XCode 6.0 it is v. 9), standard architecture - 
64-bit Intel.

Individual notes:

1. angelscript. To build angelscript use cmake:
  $ cd libsrcs/angelscript/sdk/angelscript/projects/cmake/
  $ cmake -G Xcode -DBUILD_FRAMEWORK=1 .
  $ xcodebuild -target Angelscript -configuration Release ARCHS=x86_64 ONLY_ACTIVE_ARCH=NO
  $ rm -rf ../../../../../../source/mac/Frameworks/Angelscript.framework/
  $ mv ../../lib/Release/Angelscript.framework/ ../../../../../../source/mac/Frameworks/

2. freetype. To build freetype use cmake:
  $ cd libsrcs/libfreetype/
  $ cmake -G Xcode -DBUILD_FRAMEWORK=1 .
  $ xcodebuild -target freetype -configuration Release ARCHS=x86_64 ONLY_ACTIVE_ARCH=NO
  $ rm -rf ../../source/mac/Frameworks/freetype.framework/
  $ mv ./Release/freetype.framework/ ../../source/mac/Frameworks/

3. png. To build png use cmake:
  $ cd libsrcs/libpng/
  $ cmake -G Xcode -DPNG_FRAMEWORK=1 .
  $ xcodebuild -target png16_framework -configuration Release ARCHS=x86_64 ONLY_ACTIVE_ARCH=NO
  $ rm -rf ../../source/mac/Frameworks/png.framework/
  $ mv ./Release/png.framework/ ../../source/mac/Frameworks/